<style>
  .license-name {
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: underline;
    color: var(--link-color);
  }
  .license-meta {
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
  }
</style>

<div class="content">
  <h1 style="margin-top: 4rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">License</h1>

  <p>
    dynamical.org is three things with three different licenses: this
    website, the datasets in the catalog, and the code we publish. The
    license on this page's footer only covers the first — the datasets and
    code are generally more permissively licensed, so check the specific
    section below before assuming a restriction applies to what you actually
    want to use.
  </p>

  <h3>Website</h3>
  <p>
    The prose, design, and other original content of this website (excluding
    the datasets and code described below) is licensed under
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>Datasets</h3>
  <p>
    Each dataset in the <a href="/catalog">catalog</a> states its own license
    on its catalog page and in its
    <a href="https://stac.dynamical.org/catalog.json">STAC Collection</a>
    metadata (the <code>license</code> field and <code>rel: "license"</code>
    links). Most datasets are published under
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC BY 4.0</a>, a
    permissive license that allows commercial use with attribution. Some
    carry additional terms from the originating agency (for example, ECMWF
    data), which are linked alongside the CC BY 4.0 license on that dataset's
    page.
  </p>

  <h3>Code</h3>
  <p>
    Our software repositories are published at
    <a href="https://github.com/dynamical-org">github.com/dynamical-org</a>,
    each under its own license:
  </p>
  <ul class="index-list">
  {% for repo in repos %}
    <li>
      <a href="{{ repo.url }}">
        <span class="license-name">{{ repo.name }}</span>{% if repo.description %} — {{ repo.description }}{% endif %}
        <div class="license-meta">{{ repo.license or "No license file published — all rights reserved by default" }}</div>
      </a>
    </li>
  {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <h3>Questions</h3>
  <p>
    If you're unsure whether a license covers your use case, email
    <a href="mailto:feedback@dynamical.org">feedback@dynamical.org</a>.
  </p>
</div>
